---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import Avatar from '../components/Avatar.astro';
---

<Layout title="Luke Batchelor - Developer">
  <div class="space-y-8 max-w-xl">
    <Avatar />

    <div class="space-y-3">
      <p class="text-3xl font-semibold">G'day!</p>
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        I'm Luke - a Perth-based Senior Fullstack Engineer with a decade of experience building
        things at every scale.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p class="font-semibold text-xl">Work</p>
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        Most of my career has been at Atlassian, where I helped found and scale the Frontend
        Monorepo from a single design system into a platform powering thousands of frontend packages and dozens of full scale apps (including
        Jira and Confluence). A few things I'm proud of:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-text-muted list-disc pl-5">
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-text">Changesets</span> - original author of the early
          versions of <a href="https://github.com/changesets/changesets">Changesets</a>, which has
          since been rewritten, open-sourced, and adopted across hundreds of open source projects
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-text">Landkid</span> - original co-author of Atlassian's
          frontend merge queue, a vital tool for preventing semantic conflicts in a repo that merges
          200+ PRs a day
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-text">DX & CI/CD at scale</span> - built and maintained
          hundreds of pipelines for building, testing, type-checking and deploying thousands of
          frontend packages
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-3">
      <p class="font-semibold text-xl">Home</p>
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        I'm one of the lucky people who gets to do their passion as a job and then comes home and
        keeps doing it.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        On weekends I'm almost always building something — from small games, micro-apps, PWAs and
        tools to full stack applications and automations for home, events, fundraisers, comedy
        shows, small businesses, and more.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted">A couple I'm most proud of:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-text-muted list-disc pl-5">
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-text">Generozity</span> - <a href="https://generozity.charity/">a charity platform</a> my brother and
          I built, complete with donation portal, admin interface and live OBS overlay for
          livestreams. So far it's raised over $800,000.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-text">Rap GPT</span> - a crowd + LLM powered freestyle rap
          game, built for comedian <a href="https://macshane.com.au/">Macshane</a> and performed at packed shows from Perth to Edinburgh
          Fringe.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        Other times I just love coding for the sake of it — working within creative constraints to
        see what's possible. That's led to pure CSS apps (a binary decoder, a rhythm game, a
        tic-tac-toe AI, a "mind reading app" 😂), a code-golfed Snake encoded entirely in a URL,
        and a palindromic symmetric tattoo in a profanely named esoteric programming language 😅.
      </p>
    </div>

    <a href="/projects" class="text-accent hover:underline text-sm inline-block">
      View my projects →
    </a>
  </div>
</Layout>
